I'm definitely not a tapas expert, and I'm sure there are better places than this, but for the price this was pretty good.  Highlights:  langoustines (divine -- fresh, steaming hot and nicely flavored with olive oil and salt); octopus (very fresh and nice spice to it).  Weaknesses:  cod fritters (WAY too much batter, as in "would you like some cod with your batter?").  Tuna/egg/olive salad was good, but oddly simple with not a lot of flavor.By 845pm or so it was definitely crowded.I would recommend.
